WARNING: Warning: This access token is for the gcloud CLI tool itself and is bound to its specific client ID, which requires Certificate Based Access (CBA). This means it can only be used with CBA-enabled API endpoints.

If you need a token for your own application code or scripts, you should use Application Default Credentials (ADC). Obtain an ADC token by running:
1.  gcloud auth application-default login (if you haven't already)
2.  gcloud auth application-default print-access-token

ADC tokens are intended for local development and do not have the same CBA restrictions.
